  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>
    <refpurpose>Create a new VLAN on all hosts in a pool.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>xe pool-vlan-create</command>
    </cmdsynopsis>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>xe pool-vlan-create<option> pif-uuid=&lt;param&gt;</option><option> network-uuid=&lt;param&gt;<option> vlan=&lt;param&gt;</option></option></command>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1 id="options_1">
    <title>PREREQUISITES</title>
    <para><command>xe pool-vlan-create </command>requires an internal network and one physical PIF device.</para>
    <para><command>xe pif-list</command> will list the PIFs found in a pool</para>
    <para><command>xe network-list</command> will list the networks found in a pool</para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1 id="description">
    <title>DESCRIPTION </title>
    <para><command>xe pool-vlan-create </command>creates a VLAN on all hosts in a pool and assigns it to the specified network.
A pseudo PIF is created and associated with the specified physical PIF. VLAN tagging occurs on the pseudo PIF. 
The resulting VLAN UUID is returned. </para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>REQUIRED PARAMETERS</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>network-uuid</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Network to be assigned VLAN number</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>pif-uuid</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>Physical PIF that the pseudo PIF will be associated with.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>
          <option>vlan</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>VLAN number</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>EXAMPLES</title>
    <para><command>xe vlan-create</command> <option>network-uuid=2177a448-d2c6-27f9-ca64-b3899d1cbe98</option> <option>pif-uuid=3e558a35-b5ff-c58c-eee2-388bae80cdc6</option> <option>vlan=2</option>
</para>
    <para>Output: 81e4ac23-10bc-385f-6baf-0478621297a9</para>
  </refsect1>
